src_text: Kabinete e amogetse go bolelelwa ga baagi ka kitsiso ya borataro ya Dikaelo tsa Tlhabololo ke Tona ya Lefapha la Tekolo le Tshekatsheko ya Tiro mo Kantorong ya Boporesitent Jaaka set haba se ipakaanyetsa go keteka Dingwaga di le 20 tsa Kgololosego, maAforika Borwa a tshwanetse go tlala boipelo ka gonne botshelo bo tokafetse tota fa e sale ka ngwaga wa 1994.Dikaelo di bontsha tokafalo mo dintlheng tse di botlhokwa, mme mo je lengwe, di bontsha fa re tshwanetse go dira ka natla go tobana le dikgwetlho dingwe tse di tlhagelelang ganngwe le gap Gape, dikaelo tseno, di tlhotlhetsa dipuisano ka ga dikgwetlho dingwe tse di lebaganeng le naga ya rona, ebile di dira jaaka mosupatsela wa loeto la rona mo ntshetsopeleng ya katlatleloloago le ikonom Kabinete e akgotse 41% (115) tsa dimmasepala tse di amogetseng pegelo ya matlole e e senang selabe boemong jwa dipegelo tsa boruni jwa matlole a ngwaga wa dit helete wa 2011/12.
trg_text: Cabinet s position on prominent issues in the current environment Cabinet welcomed the public launch of the sixth edition of the Development Indicators by the Minister in the Presidency for Performance Monitoring and Evaluatio As the nation prepares to celebrate 20 Years of Freedom, South Africans should be proud that life has changed for the better since 1994.The indicators show improvement in key areas and simultaneously point to the hard work still required to deal with some of our more persistent challenge Furthermore, the indicators encourage debate on the challenges our country faces and act as markers along our journey of socio-economic progres Cabinet commended the 41% (115) of municipalities that received unqualified financial statements on the 2011/2012 financial audit
